{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1770053629,"nonce":"Yz6SzYv9CmD4Wc37uTGXq+C4yMs=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87nsR0tzwAAAAU7gZmY"},"added":["documentation"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1770053630,"nonce":"1Jpq2lKh7sIMDRrH0lz7gOpR0Dg=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87nsR0tzwAAAAU7gZoY"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1770918834,"nonce":"75ytbclZuJnv+a9EdlpNbl7yo88=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87oAolN","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/132#issuecomment-3892480333"},"message":"## Design Discussion Summary\n\nAfter discussion, here's the agreed-upon design for formalizing the workspace/project config separation.\n\n### Core Concept: Two Bootstrap Patterns via `bootstrap.yaml`\n\nThe `bootstrap.yaml` file becomes self-describing, with an optional `layer` field that switches between two patterns:\n\n**Pattern A — Standalone Config Repo** (new): A dedicated repo with no ROS packages, purely workspace configuration. Cloned outside the build tree.\n\n**Pattern B — Key Repo is Also a Package** (current): The config lives inside a ROS package repo that's also built as part of a layer. This is how `unh_marine_autonomy` works today.\n\n### Updated `bootstrap.yaml` Format\n\n```yaml\ngit_url: https://github.com/example/my_project_config.git\nbranch: main\nconfig_path: config           # where to find layers.txt + repos/ within the repo\n\n# Optional: if present, clone into layers/main/\u003clayer\u003e_ws/src/\n# If absent, clone into configs/project_repo/\nlayer: core\n```\n\n### Clone Location Logic\n\n```\nHas \"layer\" field?\n  YES → layers/main/${layer}_ws/src/${repo_name}/    (Pattern B, current)\n  NO  → configs/project_repo/${repo_name}/           (Pattern A, new)\n```\n\n### Project-Level Agent Knowledge\n\nThe config repo (either pattern) can carry an `agent_context/` directory with project-wide knowledge for AI agents:\n\n```\n\u003cconfig_path\u003e/\n├── layers.txt\n├── repos/*.repos\n└── agent_context/\n    ├── project_overview.md\n    ├── conventions.md\n    └── message_types.md\n```\n\nThis gets exposed in the workspace via a single symlink:\n\n```\n.agent/project_knowledge  →  \u003cclone_location\u003e/\u003cconfig_path\u003e/agent_context/\n```\n\n- `.agent/knowledge/` remains workspace-level, fully tracked, generic ROS 2 guidance\n- `.agent/project_knowledge` is gitignored, created by `setup.sh`, points to the project's agent context\n- If no project is set up, the symlink is absent — agents see workspace knowledge only\n\n### `.repos` Files Stay Where They Are\n\nThe `.repos` files serve three consumers: workspace setup, CI, and human installation. They stay in a conventional, discoverable location within the project repo (`config/repos/` for `unh_marine_autonomy`). The `config_path` field in `bootstrap.yaml` tells `setup.sh` where to find them.\n\n### Directory Structure Overview\n\n```\nros2_agent_workspace/\n├── configs/\n│   ├── project_bootstrap.url          # Entry point URL\n│   └── project_repo/                  # Pattern A: config-only repos land here\n│       └── \u003crepo\u003e/\n│\n├── .agent/\n│   ├── knowledge/                     # Tracked, workspace-level (generic ROS 2)\n│   └── project_knowledge              # Symlink → project agent_context/ (gitignored)\n│\n└── layers/main/\n    └── core_ws/src/\n        └── unh_marine_autonomy/       # Pattern B: key repo lives here\n            └── config/\n                ├── layers.txt\n                ├── repos/*.repos\n                └── agent_context/     # Project-wide agent knowledge\n```\n\n### Key Changes Required\n\n1. **`setup.sh`**: Read `layer` and `config_path` from `bootstrap.yaml` instead of hardcoding paths. Derive clone location from `layer` presence/absence. Create `.agent/project_knowledge` symlink.\n2. **`.gitignore`**: Add `configs/project_repo/` and `.agent/project_knowledge`\n3. **`bootstrap.yaml` format**: Add `config_path` field (default: `config` or repo root)\n4. **Agent instruction files**: Reference `.agent/project_knowledge/` for project-specific context\n5. **`ARCHITECTURE.md`**: Document both patterns\n\n### Backwards Compatibility\n\n- Current `unh_marine_autonomy` bootstrap.yaml (`layer: core`) continues to work as-is\n- `config_path` defaults to `config` if not specified (matches current layout)\n- `setup.sh` remains a single entry point for both patterns\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1770925104,"nonce":"1dSTt84r7xIev2AeIpBSfAjq12g=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87nsR0tzwAAAAVLwmQQ"},"status":2}]}